FBIS3-23012 "jptot008__l94113" JPRS-TOT-94-008-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 1 March 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Explosions Rock Oil, Chemical Plants in Chechnya LD1302192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1634 GMT 13 Feb 94 LD1302192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS] [Text] Groz'ny February 13 TASS -- Overnight, explosions shattered several oil and chemical plants in the Chechen Republic of Ichkeria. According to the news agency CHECHENPRESS, shortly after midnight unidentified persons blew up three 2,000-cubic-meter tanks on the territory of the Goit-Yurt oil park on the Rostov-Baku highway between the villages of Mesker-Yurt and Belkata. Around the same time, another explosion damaged an oil pipeline on the territory of the Bufer oil park near the village of Tolstoy-Yurt. The fires caused by these explosions have been extinguished, except for one at an oil well outside the village of Vinogradnoye, 20 km of the regional capital Grozny, senior officer of the republic's fire department, Isa Khasimilov, reported.
